      "RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) is the most common model, assigning 'roles' to users and mapping 'permissions' to roles. Recommended minimum LMS role hierarchy: ① Super Admin — full system config, user management, payment access ② Training Operator — course CRUD, learner management, completion processing ③ Instructor — course content management, grading ④ Department Manager — view learning status of team members ⑤ Learner — take courses, exams, print certificates. Each role should follow the Principle of Least Privilege.",
      "ABAC (Attribute-Based Access Control) combines user attributes (department, title, location), resource attributes (content classification, security level), and environmental attributes (access time, IP, device) for dynamic access decisions. Example: 'Only HQ employees, manager-level or above, during business hours, via VPN, may view HR-linked learning reports.'",
