      "Vulnerability 1: BOLA (Broken Object Level Authorization) — Attackers modify resource IDs in API requests to access other users' data. Example: changing /api/users/123/grades to /api/users/456/grades. Defense: Server-side verification that the requester owns or has access rights to the requested resource on every endpoint.",
